4 Sandbox
*********

To run Pi inside a sandbox, customize ‘pi-executable’ and ‘pi-flags’:

     (setq pi-executable "nono")
     (setq pi-flags '("run" "--silent" "--profile" "pi" "--allow-cwd" "--" "pi"
                      "--tools" "read,bash,edit,write,grep,find,ls"))


File: pi.info,  Node: How It Works,  Next: Keybindings,  Prev: Sandbox,  Up: Top

5 How It Works
**************

Emacs starts Pi in RPC mode (documentation
(https://pi.dev/docs/latest/rpc)).  In this setup, Pi handles the agent
logic while Emacs provides the user interface.

   Some features, such as ‘/login’ and ‘/logout’, are not supported
(https://github.com/earendil-works/pi/issues/885) because they are not
currently exposed through the RPC API.


